## Target: Metasploitable 2
**Date:** 2026-05-28
**IP:** 192.168.56.101

### Finding
Port 21 — vsftpd 2.3.4 — backdoor (CVE-2011-2523)

### What It Is
A malicious backdoor was secretly introduced into the vsftpd 
2.3.4 source code in 2011. When triggered it opens a shell 
on port 6200 giving the attacker root access with no 
authentication required.

### Exploit Used
Tool: Metasploit
Module: exploit/unix/ftp/vsftpd_234_backdoor
Result: Root Meterpreter session obtained

### Impact
Full root access to the system with no credentials. An 
attacker could read all files, create backdoor accounts, 
pivot to other systems, or destroy the machine entirely.

### Patch
- Remove vsftpd 2.3.4
- Upgrade to vsftpd 3.0.5 or later
- Disable FTP entirely if not needed
- Block port 21 via firewall

### Verification
- Re-run exploit after patching
- Confirm connection is refused
